      "writtenOn": "2017-06-01T16:49:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "…and I’m not so sure about having something that’s named GetGeneralPurposeRegisters() responsible for setting these internal fields, either. It’d make more sense to do it in Initialize() (again, naming: not just InitializeBitness(), since it may also initialize the TLS address). But I see that you really want iovec::iov_len to make that determination, which wouldn’t be a natural thing to return from GetGeneralPurposeRegisters().\n\nSo how about this: pull the portion of this function concerned with getting an iovec out into an internal-only GetGeneralPurposeRegistersAndLength(), which can return the length. Call that from Initialize() and GetGeneralPurposeRegisters(). Move the rest of the is_64_bit_ and tls_address_ maintenance into Initialize().",
      "revId": "e523295436015d315e48bb13149ef100b5d3f9d3",
